  "entity": {
    "name": "Norse - Tyr",
    "mythology": "norse",
    "type": "deity",
    "icon": "‚öñÔ∏è",
    "subtitle": "God of War, Justice, and Oaths",
    "description": "The <a class=\"corpus-link\" data-term=\"One-Handed\" data-tradition=\"norse\" href=\"../corpus-search.html?tradition=norse&amp;term=tyr\" title=\"Search corpus for 'One-Handed'\">one-handed</a> god of law, justice, and honorable combat. <a class=\"corpus-link\" data-term=\"Tyr\" data-tradition=\"norse\" href=\"../corpus-search.html?tradition=norse&amp;term=tyr\" title=\"Search corpus for 'Tyr'\">Tyr</a> sacrificed his sword hand to bind the monstrous wolf <a class=\"corpus-link\" data-term=\"Fenrir\" data-tradition=\"norse\" href=\"../corpus-search.html?tradition=norse&amp;term=fenrir\" title=\"Search corpus for 'Fenrir'\">Fenrir</a>, an act of courage and self-sacrifice that exemplifies his role as guardian of cosmic order and keeper of oaths.",
    "css_colors": {}
  },
  "attributes": {},
  "mythology_stories": {
    "intro": "<a class=\"corpus-link\" data-term=\"Tyr\" data-tradition=\"norse\" href=\"../corpus-search.html?tradition=norse&amp;term=tyr\" title=\"Search corpus for 'Tyr'\">Tyr</a> is one of the oldest gods in the Norse pantheon, possibly predating <a class=\"corpus-link\" data-term=\"Odin\" data-tradition=\"norse\" href=\"../corpus-search.html?tradition=norse&amp;term=odin\" title=\"Search corpus for 'Odin'\">Odin</a> as a chief war deity. He represents the lawful and honorable aspects of warfare, in contrast to <a class=\"corpus-link\" data-term=\"Odin\" data-tradition=\"norse\" href=\"../corpus-search.html?tradition=norse&amp;term=odin\" title=\"Search corpus for 'Odin'\">Odin</a>'s more cunning and ruthless approach. <a class=\"corpus-link\" data-term=\"Tyr\" data-tradition=\"norse\" href=\"../corpus-search.html?tradition=norse&amp;term=tyr\" title=\"Search corpus for 'Tyr'\">Tyr</a>'s willingness to sacrifice himself for the greater good makes him a model of courage and integrity.",
    "key_myths": [
      {
        "name": "The Binding ofFenrir",
        "description": "<strong>The Binding of <a class=\"corpus-link\" data-term=\"Fenrir\" data-tradition=\"norse\" href=\"../corpus-search.html?tradition=norse&amp;term=fenrir\" title=\"Search corpus for 'Fenrir'\">Fenrir</a>:</strong> When the wolf <a class=\"corpus-link\" data-term=\"Fenrir\" data-tradition=\"norse\" href=\"../corpus-search.html?tradition=norse&amp;term=fenrir\" title=\"Search corpus for 'Fenrir'\">Fenrir</a> grew too dangerous, the gods commissioned the dwarves to create an unbreakable chain called <a class=\"corpus-link\" data-term=\"Gleipnir\" data-tradition=\"norse\" href=\"../corpus-search.html?tradition=norse&amp;term=gleipnir\" title=\"Search corpus for 'Gleipnir'\">Gleipnir</a>. <a class=\"corpus-link\" data-term=\"Fenrir\" data-tradition=\"norse\" href=\"../corpus-search.html?tradition=norse&amp;term=fenrir\" title=\"Search corpus for 'Fenrir'\">Fenrir</a>, suspicious of trickery, would only allow the binding if one of the gods placed their hand in his mouth as a pledge of good faith. Only <a class=\"corpus-link\" data-term=\"Tyr\" data-tradition=\"norse\" href=\"../corpus-search.html?tradition=norse&amp;term=tyr\" title=\"Search corpus for 'Tyr'\">Tyr</a> had the courage to do so. When <a class=\"corpus-link\" data-term=\"Fenrir\" data-tradition=\"norse\" href=\"../corpus-search.html?tradition=norse&amp;term=fenrir\" title=\"Search corpus for 'Fenrir'\">Fenrir</a> realized he could not break free, he bit off <a class=\"corpus-link\" data-term=\"Tyr\" data-tradition=\"norse\" href=\"../corpus-search.html?tradition=norse&amp;term=tyr\" title=\"Search corpus for 'Tyr'\">Tyr</a>'s hand at the wrist. <a class=\"corpus-link\" data-term=\"Tyr\" data-tradition=\"norse\" href=\"../corpus-search.html?tradition=norse&amp;term=tyr\" title=\"Search corpus for 'Tyr'\">Tyr</a>'s sacrifice prevented <a class=\"corpus-link\" data-term=\"Fenrir\" data-tradition=\"norse\" href=\"../corpus-search.html?tradition=norse&amp;term=fenrir\" title=\"Search corpus for 'Fenrir'\">Fenrir</a> from destroying the cosmos (until <a class=\"corpus-link\" data-term=\"Ragnarok\" data-tradition=\"norse\" href=\"../corpus-search.html?tradition=norse&amp;term=ragnarok\" title=\"Search corpus for 'Ragnarok'\">Ragnarok</a>) but cost him his sword hand - a warrior god who can no longer wield a weapon properly."
      }
    ],
